cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CV 

This paper is about domain adaptation for sentiment analysis, which is a topic that falls under the natural language processing (NLP) field. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel approach that involves learning to project embedding spaces, which is a machine learning task that falls under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves predicting sentiment, which is a task that can fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the sentiment analysis is done on visual content.
